Description:
Holiday Heaven
Tucked away in the Boomerang Way Tourist Park, this little beauty is bang for buck. Situated within short walking distance to town and Murray River, you will find this home perfect as a holiday getaway or opt to live permanently - 2 bedrooms with BIR's, bathroom with separate toilet. There's a large carport - long enough for 3 vehicles - car - boat - camper trailer if you wish. It also doubles as an secluded outdoor entertaining area for your holiday BBQ with friends and family. The Park offers all park facilities and in-ground pool, with fees being very reasonable. The town of Tocumwal has everything you need for everyday living so you can kick back and just enjoy this beautiful area and our very attractive and increasingly popular Murray River.

Description:
Popular Brooks Avenue
Located on 845m elevated block in a fantastic Barooga location, this four bedroom family home features a generous lounge and formal dining, well-appointed timber kitchen with dishwasher, electric oven, gas cooktop, pantry and ample of cupboard space. The large open plan meals/kitchen area with built in bar opens up to the rear paved patio/BBQ area - perfect for year round entertaining. All the bedrooms are of good size with built in robes and ceiling fans, the master bedroom having its own ensuite with double shower. The family bathroom has a double vanity, bath, and shower with separate toilet. The home is equipped with ducted evaporative cooling, RC/SS in the Lounge, and wall furnace gas heating in the kitchen meals area. Externally there is a double carport backing onto a double garage, securely fenced rear yard with well-established trees. This property has great potential and with a few upgrades, would suit a large family. Close proximity to all pubs, clubs and sporting facilities. Currently rented at $340 per week this home is well worth an inspection.

5 Acre Lifestyle Property
5 acre lifestyle property. Plenty of yard for children and 4 acres divided up into three yards and two paddocks including a riding arena, stable and large shed. Description:
Near New and Immaculate
A fantastic opportunity to purchase a new near home - just move your furniture in and enjoy this naturally lit home. Inside the home, the finish is of high quality and very tasteful, comprising of not one, but two living areas and a large dining/kitchen area for entertaining. For those that love to be creative in the kitchen, there's plenty of space with long benchtops, lots of storage and quality 90cm induction cooktop and 90cm fan forced oven. There's also the benefit of a large butler's pantry for extra storage and bench space. Of the three large bedrooms, the master bedroom has a beautifully appointed ensuite accessed via a walk-in-robe. Location, Lifestyle & Golf Course View
This top quality four bedroom residence is ideally positioned on a large 1173sqm block. Fronting Golf Course Road, boasting a superb outlook over the golf course fairways.
This craftsman built home features a lovely open living area with an abundant of natural light. The expansive kitchen has quality appliances, a generous breakfast bar, ample cupboard space and timber flooring.
Generous lounge, second living/ formal dining area, good sized bedrooms; main with walk-in-robe and ensuite. The home has a family sized bathroom, well appointed laundry and reverse cycle split system air conditioning throughout.

A lovely established yard providing a year round oasis with ample room for the whole family to enjoy.
A top quality home in premier location and a must to inspect.
